  "text": "The extent of CRC was classified using both the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) TNM and Union for International Cancer Control (UICC) staging systems following histopathology in all cases [CITATION_1] . Patient's demographic information including sex and age at the time of diagnosis were recorded. Cancer specific parameters including the tumor stage (pT), nodal involvement (pN), the presence or absence of distance metastases (pM), and tumor location were noted. All patients undergoing oncologic resection were included for analysis. Exclusion criteria included: palliation procedures, patients with multiple cancers, patients undergoing emergency surgery, and cases without anastomosis.",
